          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, halve the <strong>Chantenay carrots </strong>(no need to peel!) and set them aside for later</p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach </strong>under the cold tap until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can, then chop it roughly</p>",
