            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>onion marmalade</strong>, <strong>Marmite</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[340ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> stock</strong></p><p>Return the mushroom pan to a medium heat with 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[23g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>butter </strong>(or olive oil!)</p><p>Once melted, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 min or until a sandy paste remains</p><p>Gradually pour in the<strong> stock</strong>, stirring frequently, and cook for 5-6 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>onion gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
